SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16
17
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-35 of Title 2, unless there is
17
18
created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18
19
There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
19
20
for the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry to be
20
21
designated the “Oklahoma City National Memorial Education Revolving
21
22
Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
22
23
year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
23
24
Department from the sale of the Heart of the Heartland special
24
Req. No. 2695 Page 1

1
license plates authorized pursuant to Section 1135.5 of Title 47 of
1
2
the Oklahoma Statutes and legislative appropriations provided for
2
3
the purpose of providing curriculum materials and instruction on the
3
4
April 19, 1995, Alfred P. Murrah Federal Building bombing to
4
5
students in this state. All monies accruing to the credit of the
5
6
fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
6
7
Department for the purpose provided for in this section.
7
8
Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the
